Subject: [PATCH] ia64/sn2: define DMA_ATTR_WRITE_BARRIER locally in pci_dma.c

DMA_ATTR_WRITE_BARRIER (bit 0) was removed from include/linux/dma-mapping.h
when SN2 support was stripped from the kernel (commit 737e2520c), since
pci_dma.c was its only consumer.  Re-define it locally using its original
bit value, which does not conflict with any current DMA_ATTR_* flag (the
mainline attributes begin at bit 1).

This fixes a build error:

  arch/ia64/sn/pci/pci_dma.c:190:21: error: 'DMA_ATTR_WRITE_BARRIER'
  undeclared (first use in this function)

The attribute causes SN2's DMA mapping functions to use
dma_map_consistent() instead of dma_map(), configuring the SHUB hardware
for write-barrier DMA mode that forces all pending DMA writes to complete,
preventing PIO-read-before-DMA-write races on Altix interconnects.

See fix-DMA_ATTR_WRITE_BARRIER.md for full analysis.

---
 arch/ia64/sn/pci/pci_dma.c | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/ia64/sn/pci/pci_dma.c
+++ b/arch/ia64/sn/pci/pci_dma.c
@@ -18,6 +18,21 @@
 #include <asm/sn/pcidev.h>
 #include <asm/sn/sn_sal.h>
 
+/*
+ * DMA_ATTR_WRITE_BARRIER was a DMA attribute (bit 0) originally defined in
+ * include/linux/dma-mapping.h. It was an SN2-specific attribute that caused
+ * DMA mappings to use dma_map_consistent() instead of dma_map(), forcing all
+ * pending DMA writes to complete and providing strict ordering of DMA from a
+ * device across all intervening buses and bridges. It was removed from the
+ * core kernel headers when SN2 support was removed (commit 737e2520c) since
+ * SN2's pci_dma.c was its only consumer. We re-define it here locally using
+ * its original bit value, which does not conflict with any current DMA_ATTR_*
+ * flags (the mainline attributes begin at bit 1).
+ */
+#ifndef DMA_ATTR_WRITE_BARRIER
+#define DMA_ATTR_WRITE_BARRIER		(1UL << 0)
+#endif
+
 #define SG_ENT_VIRT_ADDRESS(sg)	(sg_virt((sg)))
 #define SG_ENT_PHYS_ADDRESS(SG)	virt_to_phys(SG_ENT_VIRT_ADDRESS(SG))
 
